        {
          "question": "What if my loved one's health improves and they no longer need delivery?",
          "answer": "Contact your local provider to update your loved one's status. Many programs offer congregate meal options at senior centers as a transition, allowing your loved one to maintain nutrition support while socializing with others. Reassessment can happen anytime circumstances change."
        },
        {
          "question": "Can my loved one get both Meals on Wheels and CalFresh benefits?",
          "answer": "Yes, your loved one can receive both programs simultaneously since Meals on Wheels provides prepared meals while CalFresh provides money for groceries. The combination can significantly improve nutrition security for homebound seniors with limited cooking ability."
        }
